@startuml recall-consolidate-delta-query-union
' Query union under RB_DELTA_TIER: resolve the live generation (base + its live
' deltas) from ONE snapshot, compute the contiguous-MIN frontier, search Recall
' (lsn > frontier) + base + EVERY live delta, then merge with newest-delta-wins
' dedup + tombstone suppression. Contrast recall-consolidate-query-union.puml,
' which resolves a SINGLE consolidated shard.

title Delta-tier query union: Recall + base + live deltas (RB_DELTA_TIER on)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "client" as client
participant "query_dp\n(run_query)" as dp
database "shard_catalog\n(generations)" as catalog
participant "base + live deltas\n(FAISS via SSD/RAM cache)" as gen
database "Recall\n(pgvector, recall_search)" as recall

client -> dp : POST /query {vector, top_k, filter}
activate dp

== Resolve the generation ONCE (_resolve_shard -> _generations): base + live deltas from a SINGLE snapshot ==
dp -> catalog : live_generation -> base S0 + deltas [S1..Sk]\n(one snapshot -> a consistent set; read-your-writes safe)
dp -> dp : frontier = contiguous-MIN of the deltas' covered bands\n(gap-clamped; NEVER max) -- the watermark Recall reads above

par Recall scan (worker thread)
  dp -> recall : recall_search WHERE lsn > frontier (brute-force L2^2)\n+ full recall-id set above the frontier
else base + each live delta (FAISS, L2^2, inline)
  dp -> gen : search base S0 + delta S1 .. Sk via the cache
  activate gen
  gen --> dp : per-shard hits (L2^2) + each delta's tombstone_int_ids
  deactivate gen
end

== Merge ==
dp -> dp : (1) METRIC ALIGNMENT -- square pgvector L2 -> L2^2
dp -> dp : (2) DEDUP across the generation -- NEWEST-DELTA-WINS on a repeated id\n(a re-upserted vector: keep the copy in the most-recent delta, drop the base/older one)
dp -> dp : (3) SUPPRESS -- a delta's tombstone_int_ids drop older copies of that id;\nrecall tombstones suppress their consolidated twin
dp -> dp : (4) DEDUP recall-wins -- Recall is newer than the whole generation
dp -> dp : (5) SORT ascending by L2^2, take top_k

note over dp
  Read fan-out = 1 base + up to RB_MAX_DELTAS live deltas, bounded by
  major compaction. recall@10 vs a monolithic index stays ~0.998 across 0..8 deltas.
end note

dp --> client : {matches, mode, ...}
deactivate dp

@enduml
